   "body" : "This was done on top of #17905, once/if that gets merged, will rebase the PR.\r\n\r\nOnly the last commit counts: [b0238f1](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/b0238f1022cf196b030e5c952f869c43b23782ab).\r\n\r\nRationale:\r\n\r\nAs the tip height is cached and updated via signaling in clientModel, there is no need to continue locking `cs_main` on every balance poll (`m_node.getNumBlocks()` method call).\r\n\r\nExtra topic:\r\n\r\nWould suggest to change the `cachedNumBlocks` field inside `walletModel` to a more understandable name, maybe `nLastBalanceUpdateHeight`.\r\n\r\nAnd finally, this will have the reorg equal height update issue mentioned [here](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/17905#issuecomment-577324304), whatever is presented to fix it, this should use the same flow too.\r\n\r\n[This is my first PR here, if i missed something let me know.]",
